column1: BindingDB_Patents: Inhibition Enzyme Assay. CYP (Cytochrome P450) enzymes are the major drug metabolizing enzymes present in the liver. The inhibition of CYP enzyme activity (IC50) for each of CYP1A2
column5: CYP3A4(BFC) and CYP3A4(BQ) is determined for compounds
column6: where inhibition of metabolism of a known substrate leads to a decrease in the fluorescence of the metabolized product. The fluorescence of the product is monitored as a function of compound concentration.Compounds are dissolved in DMSO to a concentration of 100 mM. These are diluted 1 uL into 82 uL of acetonitrile. An 11 uL aliquot of this solution is then added to 204 uL of cofactor mix (1.3% NADPH Regeneration system Solution A
column7: 1.04% NADPH Regeneration system Solution B from BD Biosciences
column8: 5% acetonitrile and 0.05% DMSO). These are then serially diluted 1:1 (160 uL to 160 uL co-factor mix) for a total of 10 points. A 10 uL aliquot of this final mixture is dispensed into 384 well assay plates.
